snippet.textDisplay: I love you man! I know we've never even been in the same room together, but the smiles and feeling of joy you provide can really only be equivocated to the emotional joy I feel from what I would consider love. Sure, it may be anecdotal because I'm drawing heavy conclusions only from what I know of you from the Office and now SGN. But isn't that the entire premise and goal of entertainment, to spark an emotional response. So many are quick to dismiss the feeling of attachment to entertainers. But I welcome it because often, these type of feeling take lots of time and lots of effort to develop and some days, I'm just lonely and want to feel something, anything, and whether or not these feelings are anecdotal and not based on a reciprocating relationship, our subconscious reward center doesn't know the difference. Don't get me wrong, I'm very aware that since we don't have a reciprocating relationship, this is not a means or way of replacing real relationships and needs, desiring to put that effort in with people. But regardless, what you do for me and millions other is VERY tremendous, I don't know how much you realize this, so I don't want to assume you "just don't know." But for a quick perspective, I know you say you're just providing news. But its human instinct to decipher and make new things distinct. So the fact so many people notice this, notice what you are doing, its because we lack this positivity and most of the people everyone encounters do not give positive energy. So sure, if you read about this in an essay, academically it is pretty mundane. But emotions don't care how complicated or technical something is. its often the smallest things that bring the most joy but are often overlooked cause they are, well, small and simple. And if we instead use a happiness index to evalute impact, my friend, YOU"VE CHANGED THE WORLD FOR BETTER! But if you were not humble about this too than you probably wouldnt be the awesome guy who is able to fill a persons heart with joy! So thank you! THANK YOU my friend! Thank You!!!

snippet.textDisplay: @somegoodnews this is the best thing ever.  I'm one of the lucky ones, and it isn't lost on me.  I have an awesome job I can do from home; I have food and shelter, and I live in a grossly affluent part of Atlanta - and lately an area that you never saw homelessness is crawling with it.  I go on walks in the evening with my dogs and boyfriend and I choke back tears as I see the steps of churches becoming a home to people who have none, benches that have been taken for homes to those with none, and I cry, and I come home and try to be grateful because I know I'm fortunate...but my heart breaks to see this, literally in my back yard, steps from my house... so THANK YOU, you're an angel and funny and wonderful.  The world needs more people just like you.
